# Pattern Selection Guide

## Quick Reference

### Common Decisions

1. Component Selection
2. State Management
3. Data Fetching
4. Form Handling
5. Error Handling

## Decision Trees

### Component Selection

```mermaid
graph TD
    A[New UI Element] --> B{Primitive UI?}
    B -->|Yes| C[Use Radix UI]
    B -->|No| D{Common Pattern?}
    D -->|Yes| E[Use Shadcn UI]
    D -->|No| F{Feature Specific?}
    F -->|Yes| G[Create Feature Component]
    F -->|No| H[Create Shared Component]
```

### State Management

```mermaid
graph TD
    A[New State] --> B{URL Sharable?}
    B -->|Yes| C[Use URL State]
    B -->|No| D{Server Data?}
    D -->|Yes| E[Use TanStack Query]
    D -->|No| F{Form State?}
    F -->|Yes| G[Use TanStack Form]
    F -->|No| H{Global UI?}
    H -->|Yes| I[Use Zustand]
    H -->|No| J[Use React State]
```

### Data Fetching

```mermaid
graph TD
    A[Data Need] --> B{Read or Write?}
    B -->|Read| C{Real-time?}
    B -->|Write| D[Use Mutation]
    C -->|Yes| E[Use Subscription]
    C -->|No| F{Dependent?}
    F -->|Yes| G[Use Dependent Query]
    F -->|No| H[Use Basic Query]
```

### Form Handling

```mermaid
graph TD
    A[New Form] --> B{Complex Form?}
    B -->|Yes| C[Use TanStack Form]
    B -->|No| D{Need Validation?}
    D -->|Yes| E[Use Zod + Form]
    D -->|No| F[Use Basic Form]
```

### Error Handling

```mermaid
graph TD
    A[Error Case] --> B{User Facing?}
    B -->|Yes| C[Use Error Boundary]
    B -->|No| D{API Error?}
    D -->|Yes| E[Use Query Error]
    D -->|No| F[Use Try-Catch]
```

## Pattern Selection Matrix

### UI Components

| Need              | Pattern          | When to Use                 |
| ----------------- | ---------------- | --------------------------- |
| Basic UI Element  | Radix UI         | Need primitive component    |
| Common UI Pattern | Shadcn UI        | Need pre-built component    |
| Feature UI        | Custom Component | Need specific functionality |
| Layout            | Layout Component | Need page structure         |

### State Management

| Need            | Pattern        | When to Use          |
| --------------- | -------------- | -------------------- |
| URL State       | Router State   | Need shareable state |
| Server State    | TanStack Query | Need backend data    |
| Form State      | TanStack Form  | Need form handling   |
| Global UI State | Zustand        | Need global UI state |
| Local State     | React State    | Need component state |

### Data Operations

| Need              | Pattern         | When to Use          |
| ----------------- | --------------- | -------------------- |
| Data Fetching     | Basic Query     | Need to read data    |
| Data Updates      | Mutation        | Need to write data   |
| Real-time Updates | Subscription    | Need live updates    |
| Dependent Data    | Dependent Query | Need sequential data |

## Implementation Guidelines

### 1. Component Implementation

```typescript
// Decision: Feature-specific component
export function UserProfile({ id }: { id: string }) {
  // Implementation
}

// Decision: Shared component
export function Button({ children, ...props }: ButtonProps) {
  // Implementation
}
```

### 2. State Management

```typescript
// Decision: URL state
const router = useRouter();
const { id } = router.params;

// Decision: Server state
const query = useQuery({
  queryKey: ['data'],
  queryFn: fetchData,
});

// Decision: Form state
const form = useForm({
  defaultValues: { name: '' },
});

// Decision: Global state
const useStore = create<Store>((set) => ({
  theme: 'light',
  setTheme: (theme) => set({ theme }),
}));
```

### 3. Data Operations

```typescript
// Decision: Basic query
const query = useQuery({
  queryKey: ['users'],
  queryFn: fetchUsers,
});

// Decision: Mutation
const mutation = useMutation({
  mutationFn: updateUser,
  onSuccess: () => {
    // Handle success
  },
});
```

## Best Practices

1. **Pattern Selection**

   - Start with decision trees
   - Consider requirements
   - Check constraints
   - Review alternatives

2. **Implementation**

   - Follow patterns exactly
   - Include all aspects
   - Test thoroughly
   - Document decisions

3. **Maintenance**
   - Monitor usage
   - Gather feedback
   - Update patterns
   - Review decisions

## Anti-Patterns

1. **Component Anti-Patterns**

   - Mixing concerns
   - Prop drilling
   - Deep component trees
   - Inline styles

2. **State Anti-Patterns**

   - State duplication
   - Prop drilling
   - Context overuse
   - Global state overuse

3. **Data Anti-Patterns**
   - Direct API calls
   - Missing error handling
   - Improper caching
   - Nested queries

